56 existing state law, including, without limitation, demolishing the homes in the
57 Windsor Park neighborhood for the purposes of creating the public park required
58 under the Act; and (13) authorizes that entity to retain or reuse existing
59 infrastructure rather than demolish such infrastructure under certain circumstances.
60 Section 4 of this bill removes the requirement for the Housing Division to pay
61 moving expenses and restitution to owners of single-family residences in the
62 Windsor Park neighborhood from certain Community Development Block Grant
63 funds transferred to the Housing Division and, instead, authorizes those funds to be
64 used by the Housing Division to pay relocation expenses for certain owners and
65 tenants.
66 Section 5 of this bill provides that money appropriated from the State General
67 Fund for the purposes of the Act reverts at the end of the 2025-2027 biennium
68 rather than at the end of the 2023-2025 biennium.
69 Section 6 of this bill appropriates $25,000,000 from the State General Fund to
70 the Housing Division for the purposes of the Act.
